<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/187a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-06T14:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>216. Please obtain and mail at the very earliest opportunity an
                                official map showing specifically the boundaries of the group of
                                islands, keys and rocks in the West Indies over which Denmark claims
                                sovereignty and which she cedes to the United States under the
                                pending treaty. This map should be the official expression of the
                                Government of Denmark as to the geographic limits of the Danish West
                                Indies.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>